To install on a DHCP server
become root and run:
    cd /cdg/dist
    svn co https://svn.ita.chalmers.se/repos/adhoc/trunk/adhoc-connect
    cd adhoc-connect
    ./install.sh
    
To upgrade a DHCP server:
become root and run:
    cd /cdg/dist/adhoc-connect
    svn up
    ./install.sh
    
When svn asks for password for root, just return and svn will ask for your username, enter your cid and your cid password.
Say no to saving the password in cleartext.

Note: You may have to get access to the SVN repository. Send the URL to teamunix@ita.chalmers.se and ask for permission.